\parai{Usability} references the ease with which users can request the information they need. SEs and LLMs are based on natural language, which greatly boosts their usability; they ``speak'' our language. Conversely, to exploit the full power of KGs, users must write structured queries 
 in a formal language: a high barrier for many.
 Thus, while users often interact directly with SEs and LLMs, users most often interact indirectly with KGs via end-user 
 applications.
 On the positive side, natural language interfaces that map user questions (e.g., ``Which Turing Award winners were born in Latin America?'') into structured queries (e.g., Cypher, SPARQL, etc.) are being advanced to improve KG usability.